## MUST

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Module layout | `backend/src/modules/<domain>/` (`routes/` â†’ `services/` â†’ `repositories/`) |
| Tenant scope | Every business query includes `tenant_id`; repositories extend `TenantRepository` |
| GL writes | `FinancialPostingService` only |
| API prefix | `/api/v1` via `mountVersionedApi.ts` |
| Mutations audit | `withAudit()` or `recordDomainMutation()` |
| Real-time sync | After commit: `emitEntityEvent()` or `emitFinancialPosted()` + client invalidation |
| LWW | `checkEntityLwwConflict()`; HTTP 409 + `serverVersion` on conflict |
| Shared logic | Calculations in `shared/financial-core/` or `shared/report-engines/` only |
| Migrations | `database/migrations/NNN_snake_case.sql` (PostgreSQL only) |
| Permissions | `shared/rbac/permissions.ts` â†’ `npm run build:backend` |
| API client | `apiClient` base `/api/v1` |
| Explicit tenantId | From `req.tenantId` â€” never client-supplied |
| PostgreSQL only | All new data access via module repositories |

## MUST NOT

- SQL in route handlers
- Direct journal/GL writes outside `FinancialPostingService`
- Missing `tenant_id` in queries
- Edit AUTO-GENERATED `backend/src/financial/` or `backend/src/auth/permissions.ts`
- New report math in `components/`
- Broad `useAppContext()` in new UI
- New endpoints on legacy `/api` (alias removed)
- SQLite, `sqliteBridge`, `VITE_LOCAL_ONLY`, `services/database/` for new work
- New flat routes or flat services
- Local-only state updates; manual refresh as primary sync
- Unscoped socket broadcasts
- Commit `.env*`, `backend/dist/`, backups

## Real-Time First (mandatory)

Multi-user ERP â€” every business mutation must propagate to all connected clients in the same tenant. A feature without synchronization support is **incomplete**. See `03_realtime_sync.mdc`.

## Core business domains

First-class domains under `backend/src/modules/`: Project Construction, Contracts, BOQ, IPC Bills, Retention, Variations, Purchase Orders, Vendor Quotations, Property Sales, Property Rentals, CRM, Collections, Facility Management.

## Full-stack feature flow

```
migration â†’ TenantRepository â†’ service â†’ route â†’ mountVersionedApi â†’ *Api.ts â†’ hook (+ socket) â†’ UI
```

Mutations: audit + `emitEntityEvent()`. GL: `FinancialPostingService`.

## Enforcement

If a request violates architecture:

1. Explain the violation
2. Propose the compliant implementation
3. Refuse non-compliant architecture unless user explicitly accepts risk after explanation

